      <hedline>
        <hl1>CINAR HIRES ADVISER</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By James Brooke</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Brooke, James</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Cinar Corp, troubled Montreal animation company, hires Merrill Lynch as financial adviser and hints at possible sale (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Hinting of a possible sale, Cinar, the troubled Montreal animation company, said it had hired Merrill Lynch as a financial adviser. Cinar, creator of the Emmy-award winning ''Arthur'' series, suspended stock trading March 9 after allegations emerged that it had earned millions of dollars in Canadian government tax credits for falsely reporting American script writers as Canadians.</p>
        <p>James Brooke</p>
      </block>
